race.comment: LUCKY I AM (4) was only gunned down late at her last start 28 days ago over this track and trip and gets the Winkers on today replacing the Blinkers. She has enough early speed to offset the wide draw and if she gets across easy enough, she'll be very hard to run down. ROMMEL'S GODDESS (7) has been impressive since joining the Barton stable, raising the bar again here a fortnight ago. She's never missed the placings at 1200m and this sets up perfectly from the barrier. Can go one better this time around. SNIPPY WHICH (2) closed strongly last start over 1100m and should be better suited by the slight rise in trip here. CJP has a good record when riding this gelding and another strong showing is on the cards. SPANK APPEAL (5) was solid in her recent trial and the blinkers go on today. Can pick up where she left off. AMARLIME (8) can improve on what she showed fresh.
